1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 15.1-01 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to review of public school compliance with state law.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 15.1-01 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
5 and enacted as follows:
6 Public schools - Compliance review - Determination by attorney general.
7 1. An interested person may submit to the state board of public school education a
8 request for review to determine whether a school district is in compliance with an
9 education-related state statute.
10 2. A request for review must be submitted in the manner prescribed by the state board of
11 public school education. The state board of public school education shall develop a
12 form for an interested person to initiate the review process.
13 3. A school district shall provide to the public on the school district website the form
14 under subsection 2 and instructions to submit the request for review .
15 4. The attorney general shall:
16 a. Review the information submitted by the interested person, investigate as
17 necessary, and determine whether a school district is in compliance with an
18 education-related state statute; or
19 b. Dismiss a request for review if the request for review exceeds the purpose of this
20 section or fails to meet the requirements of the state board of public school
21 education.
