1 5. If the attorney general finds the school district is failing to comply with an education-
2 related state statute, the attorney general shall advise the school district of the findings
3 and provide instructions on how to comply with the statute.
4 6. The attorney general's findings are prima facie evidence in an adjudicative proceeding
5 under chapter 28 - 32 .
6 7. The state board of public school education, with the attorney general, may adopt rules
7 to implement this section.
